  "description": "Annual herb from Asteraceae, domesticated by Indigenous North American cultures ~3500 BCE. Heliotropic seedlings track the sun via differential growth on the stem; mature capitula exhibit solar tracking via pulvinus-driven petiolar movement. Accumulates helianthic acid and polyunsaturated oils in achene; yellow and purple xanthophyll pigments in ray florets. Ecological role as primary pollinator attractant and seed-oil staple.",
